            <h2>Calibration</h2>
            <p>Proper calibration is critical for the accuracy and quality of 3D prints. Below are the key calibration steps recommended for most 3D printers:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Bed Leveling:</strong> Ensures that the printing bed is perfectly horizontal. Manufacturers often recommend manual or automatic bed leveling processes. Consistent leveling is crucial to avoid issues like poor adhesion and warping.</li>
                <li><strong>Nozzle Calibration:</strong> Ensure that the nozzle height is correctly set relative to the bed. This might involve adjusting the Z-offset.</li>
                <li><strong>Extruder Calibration:</strong> Verifying that the filament is being extruded consistently. Run tests to measure flow rates and adjust steps per millimeter as necessary.</li>
                <li><strong>Temperature Calibration:</strong> Both the extruder and bed temperature affect print quality. Use calibration prints to determine the ideal temperature settings for specific filament types.</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Example: Manual Bed Leveling Process</h3>
            <pre>
1. Home the printer and disable stepper motors.
2. Place a sheet of paper on the bed.
3. Move the nozzle to each corner manually.
4. Adjust the bed screws until there is a slight resistance when moving the paper.
5. Repeat for center and in-between points as needed.
            </pre>
        </section>
