            <h2>What to Do After Changing Filament</h2>
            <p>Changing filament is a routine task, but it requires careful attention to ensure continued print quality. Follow these steps after changing the filament:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Prime the Extruder:</strong> Run a simple extrude command to ensure the new filament is flowing consistently. Remove any remnants of the old filament before starting a new print.
                </li>
                <li><strong>Check for Clogs:</strong> If the new filament is a different material, clear any blockages that might have formed in the nozzle by performing a cold pull or using a cleaning filament.
                </li>
                <li><strong>Temperature Adjustment:</strong> Adjust the extruder temperature based on the new filament's specifications. Some materials require pre-heating or a different temperature profile.
                </li>
                <li><strong>Calibration Check:</strong> Consider running a calibration print after a filament change to verify that the extrusion rate and heating are optimal.
                </li>
                <li><strong>Software Update:</strong> Update your slicing software settings if the new filament has different printing parameters.
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>
